<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,152,1100]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Remarks. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ogloblin" box="[318,507,874,900]" firstAuthor="Ogloblin" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="84 - 111" refId="ref11788" refString="Ogloblin, D. A. (1930) De quelques especes de Halticinae (Col. Chrysomelidae) de la collection de V. Motschulsky. Museo Nacional de Sciences Naturales Madrid, 10, 84 - 111." type="journal article" year="1930">Ogloblin (1930)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[679,905,875,900]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[679,905,875,900]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Phaelota variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Motschulsky)" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[972,1312,874,900]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis box="[972,1130,875,900]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. flavipennis</emphasis>
(Motschulsky)
</taxonomicName>
. Comparison of the 
<typeStatus box="[284,375,914,940]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[421,566,915,940]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[421,566,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[650,810,915,940]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis box="[650,810,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed important characters that reliably separate these two species (see the key below) and we therefore recognize 
<taxonomicName box="[923,1064,955,980]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[923,1064,955,980]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid. In the key this species is in the same couplet with 
<emphasis box="[473,637,995,1020]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[473,633,995,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">P. flavipennis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
from which it can be easily differentiated by the median lobe of the aedeagus with two abruptly ending impressions basally (
